<paragraph id="E07536B6FF38FF5E5889FAD7FBDE677A" blockId="245.[151,1437,1045,1540]" pageId="245" pageNumber="246">
REMARKS: 
<bibRefCitation id="845B4B47FF38FF5E5914FAD4FE55640A" author="Rondani, C." box="[266,486,1369,1396]" pageId="245" pageNumber="246" refId="ref368401" refString="Rondani, C. (1857) Dipterologiae italicae prodromus. Vol: II. Species italicae ordinis dipterorum in genera characteribus definita, ordinatim collectae, methodo analitica distinctae, et novis vel minus cognitis descriptis. Pars prima. Oestridae: Syrphfidae [sic!]: Conopidae. A. Stocchi, Parmae [= Parma], 264 pp., 1 pl. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 8160" type="book" year="1857">Rondani (1857: 43)</bibRefCitation>
described both sexes of 
<taxonomicName id="27CA4D35FF38FF5E5AE5FAD4FC09640A" box="[763,954,1369,1395]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Eristalis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="245" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="saltuum">
<emphasis id="D2BEEAA4FF38FF5E5AE5FAD4FC09640A" box="[763,954,1369,1395]" italics="true" pageId="245" pageNumber="246">Eristalis saltuum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without specifying either the 
<taxonomicName id="27CA4D35FF38FF5E5D14FAD4FAD3640A" box="[1290,1376,1369,1395]" family="Number" pageId="245" pageNumber="26" rank="family">number</taxonomicName>
of or the length of the specimens: “ 
<emphasis id="D2BEEAA4FF38FF5E5A06FAF3FD0264C2" italics="true" pageId="245" pageNumber="246">
Marem bis obtinui ex alpibus pedemontanis, 
<taxonomicName id="27CA4D35FF38FF5E5C0DFAF3FB8E64EE" box="[1043,1085,1406,1431]" class="Insecta" family="Flatidae" genus="Doria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="245" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="una">una</taxonomicName>
vice a D. 
<taxonomicName id="27CA4D35FF38FF5E5CACFAF3FAF464EE" box="[1202,1351,1405,1431]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Truqui" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="245" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="altera">Truqui altera</taxonomicName>
a Prof. Bellardi. Foeminam a Tiguro D. Bremi misit
</emphasis>
” [I obtained the male twice from the 
<collectingRegion id="220EF854FF38FF5E5C4EFA2CFB0864C2" box="[1104,1211,1441,1467]" country="Italy" name="Piemonte" pageId="245" pageNumber="246">Piedmont</collectingRegion>
Alps, once from Dr. Truqui, the second time from Prof. Bellardi. Dr. Bremi sent the female from Tigurum]”. We found 
<specimenCount id="F6CCFD3FFF38FF5E5D38FA48FA2F64A6" box="[1318,1436,1477,1503]" pageId="245" pageNumber="246" type="male">three male</specimenCount>
<typeStatus id="3F718814FF38FF5E58D9FA67FE9A677D" box="[199,297,1514,1540]" pageId="245" pageNumber="246">syntypes</typeStatus>
in this study. The female was not found in this study and is presumed lost.
</paragraph>
